Popular Ghanaian actress, Yvonne Nelson has absolved Satan of all suffering by the masses The movie maker blamed politicians for making the lives of her countrymen difficult. Nelson called on President Nana Akufo-Addo to quit talking too much and act fast in alleviating the suffering of the people. Sharing a video of a mother taking her child to school through a dilapidated wooden bridge, the award-winning actress wrote: “Mr President @NAkufoAddo , you need to ACT fast! We need action! Do! The TALK is too much! Imagine that was your grandchild going to school.”   I want to sell my vote, says Okon Lagos     More women now abuse men – Emeka Ike     2023: Lady dumps boyfriend for not supporting Obi   In another tweet, she wrote: “You think satan is on earth making your life difficult? It’s the politicians, I can assure you of that!” Reacting to the comments elicited by her tweets, the star actress opined her countrymen truly deserved the ill treatment being meted out to them, vowing to block anyone with biased opinions in the comment section. “From the comments, you’d understand why the people keep suffering. The people themselves pamper politicians. I guess you all deserve how they treat you then. I pray you receive sense! I will block you if you bring your partisan self here,” she added.